# Development Workflow

This document outlines the development workflow for LocalCA.

## Getting Started

1. Clone the repository
2. Create a password file: `echo "your-secure-password" > cakey.txt`
3. Start the backend:
   - Windows: `run-dev.bat`
   - Linux/macOS: `./run-dev.sh`
4. Start the frontend: `pnpm dev`
5. Access the web interface at http://localhost:3000

## Project Structure

- Backend (Go):
  - [main.go](mdc:main.go) - Entry point
  - [pkg/](mdc:pkg) - Core packages
  - [go.mod](mdc:go.mod) - Go module definition
- Frontend (Next.js):
  - [app/](mdc:app) - Next.js app directory
  - [components/](mdc:components) - React components
  - [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts

## Development Scripts

- `pnpm dev` - Start Next.js development server
- `pnpm build` - Build the Next.js application
- `pnpm start` - Start the production Next.js server
- `go run main.go` - Run the Go backend
- `run-dev.sh` / `run-dev.bat` - Start the backend with development settings

## Docker Development

- `docker-compose up` - Start both backend and frontend
- `docker-compose up backend` - Start only the backend
- `docker-compose up frontend` - Start only the frontend
- `docker-compose build` - Rebuild the Docker images

